<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-42-0137 </DOCNO><TEXT>Coal production in the USA is up 0.3% by the end of September 1987 fromthe pace of one year ago. Most impressive has been the growth in demandat power plants where coal consumption is up by 13.5 million tons throughthe month of July. The coal markets turnabout is based upon the entireeconomic spectrum not upon a single large market. US steel mills representintense power consuming activities as do the US chemicals, plastics,paper and pulp industries.</TEXT></DOC>